###Writing an equation

Our $\maroonD{\text{whole}}$ is the item's price $\maroonD{p}$, and the $\blueE{\text{part}}$ is how much money Marta pays $(\blueE{t})$ with the $\goldE{8}\%$ tax:

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{\goldE{n}}{100} \cdot \maroonD{\text{whole}} &= \blueE{\text{part}}
\\\\
\dfrac{\goldE{8}}{100} \cdot \maroonD{p} &= \blueE{t}
\\\\
0.08 \maroonD{p} &= \blueE{t}
\\\\
\blueE{t} &= 0.08 \maroonD{p}
\end{align}$

###Writing an equation

Since Seb bikes at constant rate of $\blueE{20}$ kilometers per hour, let's substitute that for $\blueE{\text{rate}}$. Then, we can solve for $\maroonD{\text{distance}}$ ($\maroonD{d}$) in terms of $\goldE{\text{time}}$ ($\goldE{t}$):

$\begin{align}
\blueE{\text{rate}} &= \dfrac{\maroonD{\text{distance}}}{\goldE{\text{time}}}
\\\\
\blueE{20} &= \dfrac{\maroonD{d}}{\goldE{t}}
\\\\
\goldE{t} \cdot \blueE{20} &= \dfrac{\maroonD{d}}{\cancel{\goldE{t}}} \cdot \cancel{\goldE{t}}
\\\\
\blueE{20} \goldE{t} &= \maroonD{d}
\\\\
\maroonD{d} &= \blueE{20} \goldE{t}
\end{align}$

